cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.HC

The paper proposes a novel method for detecting subject and condition specific structural alterations in neuroimaging data. The method combines techniques from classification, generalization error estimation, and image restoration. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories.
